		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />MMC5 is still to this day one of the less-understood mappers (compared to others).  Keep in mind the variance in MMC3 IRQ counter behaviour literally took years to figure out (over the course of almost 2 decades).  Just some context.  What I'm saying is, it doesn't surprise me that a quirk of this nature would exist for a long period of time.

		

